EXPLANATORY DATA ANALYSIS

From the above plots, it can be inferred that:

1.Sub-saharan Africa has the highest participations.Middle East and North Africa accounted for the lowest              participations.
2.In all regions, the largest propotion of all ventures has website, with all ventures in Europe and Central
  Asia having websites, while in Sub-Saharan Africa, approximately 50% of the total ventures have no website.
3.Agriculture sector has the highest ventures in all regions, with highest contribution in sub-saharan Africa.
  The other popular ventures are Education and 'Others'
4.Venture  growth from the year 2000 was relatively slow upto the year 2008. Exponential growth was noticed          from the year 2009 to 2014, with a slight drop in the year 2015. A drastic drop was recorded in 2016.
5.Majority of the venture proprietors are aged between 26-40 years.
6.Age didn't contibute to the investment sector. Agriculture is the most popular choice among all ages.
7.Most of the ventures made a profit ranging between 0%-5%.
8.Lastly, agriculture is the popular venture in all profit categories.
